Definition: A nucleoside 5'-monophosphate(2<minus/>) that results from the removal of two protons from the phosphate group of adenosine 5'-monophosphate (AMP).
A nucleoside 5'-diphosphate(3<minus/>) arising from deprotonation of all three diphosphate OH groups of adenosine 5'-diphosphate (ADP); major species present at pH 7.3.
